# The Name Collision

Sometimes, the parameters you pass into a Constructor have the EXACT SAME name as the Properties already living in the class.

```dart
class User {
  String name;

  User(String name) {
    name = name; // Wait... what?
  }
}
```
Dart gets confused. Are you assigning the parameter to the property? Or the parameter to itself?

## Pointing to Self

The `this` keyword is how an object points directly at its own properties, completely bypassing parameters.
`this.name` literally translates to: **"THIS object's property called name"**.

```dart
class User {
  String name;

  User(String name) {
    this.name = name; 
  }
}
```
It reads: Put the parameter 'name' into THIS object's 'name' property.
